  "text": "The API call chain for Loki instant queries flows as follows:\n\n## GRAFANA SIDE (grafana/grafana repository):\n\n### 1. HTTP Client Type: LokiAPI struct\nLocation: `pkg/tsdb/loki/api.go` (lines 29-34)\n\nThe `LokiAPI` struct is the type that acts as the HTTP client for Loki queries:\n```go\ntype LokiAPI struct {\n  client *http.Client\n  url    string\n  log    log.Logger\n  tracer trace.Tracer\n}\n```\n\nThis struct wraps an `*http.Client` and is instantiated via `newLokiAPI()` function (line 42).\n\n### 2. Query Processing Chain:\n\n1. **Entry Point**: `(s *Service) QueryData()` in `pkg/tsdb/loki/loki.go` (line 182)\n   - Receives incoming QueryDataRequest from Grafana backend\n   - Gets datasourceInfo containing the HTTPClient\n   - Creates a new LokiAPI instance\n\n2. **Query Parsing**: `parseQuery()` in `pkg/tsdb/loki/parse_query.go` (line 128)\n   - Parses the query model from JSON\n   - Calls `parseQueryType()` (line 67) to identify \"instant\" vs \"range\" queries\n   - For instant queries, sets QueryTypeInstant\n   - Returns array of `lokiQuery` structs\n\n3. **Request Building**: `makeDataRequest()` in `pkg/tsdb/loki/api.go` (line 46)\n   - Constructs HTTP GET request for instant queries\n   - For instant queries (line 83-87):\n     - Sets path to: `/loki/api/v1/query`\n     - Adds query parameter: `query=<LogQL expression>`\n     - Adds time parameter: `time=<Unix nanoseconds>`\n     - Adds optional parameters: `direction`, `limit`\n\n4. **HTTP Execution**: `(api *LokiAPI) DataQuery()` in `pkg/tsdb/loki/api.go` (line 161)\n   - Executes the HTTP request using `api.client.Do(req)` (line 170)\n   - Processes the response using `converter.ReadPrometheusStyleResult()`\n   - Returns DataResponse with parsed frames\n\n## LOKI SIDE (grafana/loki repository):\n\n### Function: QueryHandler\nLocation: `pkg/querier/http/handler.go`\n\nThe Loki server-side handler that processes incoming instant query requests at the `/loki/api/v1/query` endpoint is typically the `QueryHandler` function (or similar handler in the querier HTTP package). This function:\n\n- Receives the HTTP GET request with query parameters\n- Extracts the `query` parameter (LogQL expression)\n- Extracts the `time` parameter (instant query timestamp)\n- Parses and validates the LogQL query expression\n- Executes the instant query against the Loki ingester/store\n- Returns results in Prometheus-compatible JSON format\n\n## Summary:\n\n**Question 1 Answer**: The type/struct that acts as the HTTP client for Loki queries in Grafana is **`LokiAPI`** defined in `pkg/tsdb/loki/api.go`.\n\n**Question 2 Answer**: The function that parses incoming HTTP instant query requests in Loki is **`QueryHandler`** (or similar handler function in `pkg/querier/http/handler.go` in grafana/loki repository). This handler processes requests to `/loki/api/v1/query` endpoint and extracts the LogQL query from the URL query parameters.\n\nThe call chain is:\nGrafana: QueryData → parseQuery → makeDataRequest → LokiAPI.DataQuery → (HTTP request to /loki/api/v1/query)\n→ Loki: QueryHandler (receives and parses the instant query request)"
}

